      "id": "ch-space-opt",
      "title": "Space Optimization",
      "description": "The standard implementation uses O(n) extra space for the min stack. Can you optimize to only store a new min when the pushed value is ≤ current minimum? What's the worst case space usage of the optimized version?",
      "type": "optimize"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch-max-stack",
      "title": "MaxStack",
      "description": "Modify the MinStack design to support getMax() in O(1) instead. Then extend it to support both getMin() AND getMax() simultaneously. What changes?",
      "type": "scenario"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch-break-invariant",
      "title": "Break the Min Stack",
      "description": "What happens if you forget to pop the min stack when calling pop() on the main stack? Walk through an example sequence where this bug causes getMin() to return the wrong value.",
      "type": "break-it"
    }
